<item>
            <title>[LU-8610] Better handle of HW dependency of DLC configuration</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8610</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While testing &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5050&quot; title=&quot;cpu partitioning oddities&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5050&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5050&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; the old configuration for my DLC stopped working and it reported the error:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;771343.391364&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; LustreError: 138538:0:(libcfs_string.c:466:cfs_expr_list_values()) Number of values 4 exceeds max allowed 16 &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;771343.391507&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; LNetError: 138538:0:(config.c:172:lnet_ni_alloc()) Failed to set CPTs for NI o2ib1: -22&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Which is not clear what is wrong.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Any DLC setup with changing CPT partition setup.</environment>
