                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="177928" author="ashehata" created="Thu, 15 Dec 2016 20:47:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Question: when you configure the CPTs in modprobe and you change cpu_pattern as you mentioned, is it handled differently? or do you have to match the network CPT configuration in the modprobe configuration as well?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="177757" author="dmiter" created="Wed, 14 Dec 2016 20:01:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Amir, just create (export) DLC configuration with few numbers of CPTs and then reduce the count of them and try to load previous DLC configuration.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example, create DLC configuration with&#160;&lt;b&gt;cpu_pattern=&quot;&quot;&lt;/b&gt; and then try to load it with&#160;&lt;b&gt;cpu_pattern=&quot;N&quot;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="177732" author="ashehata" created="Wed, 14 Dec 2016 17:01:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This fell through the cracks for me. Can you please provide your DLC configuration.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="166909" author="yujian" created="Thu, 22 Sep 2016 15:06:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Amir,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Do you have any progress on this ticket? Thank you.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="166000" author="pjones" created="Wed, 14 Sep 2016 13:08:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Amir&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Any suggestions here?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
